nts":[],"created_at":1784776562456426001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Problem\nA source citation [rebar:<id>] from a child requires a DIRECT verified edge from the citing ticket to the cited target; a transitive/inherited edge does not satisfy it. Combined with link's hierarchy promotion (blocking deps on a story are promoted to the parent epic by design), a child's citation to a prerequisite is left ungrounded with no obvious cause.\n\n## Design (per maintainer)\nCitation validation must honor INHERITED links. Epic A has Child B; Child B cites Epic C. Epics depend on Epics and Stories depend on Stories. So as long as Epic A (B's parent) depends_on Epic C, the citation in Child B to Epic C is valid via inheritance from the parent's edge.\n\n## Fix\nWhen validating a [rebar:<id>] citation from a ticket T to target X, treat the citation as grounded if EITHER (a) T has a direct verified edge to X (current behavior), OR (b) an ancestor of T (walk parent_id chain) has a direct verified depends_on/blocking edge to X (or to an ancestor of X at the matching hierarchy level). Preserve current direct-edge behavior; only ADD the inherited path.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A citation from Child B to Epic C is VALID when B's parent Epic A depends_on Epic C, with no direct B->C edge.\n- A citation with neither a direct nor an inherited edge remains INVALID (no over-grounding).\n- Existing direct-edge citations remain valid (no regression).\n- Tests cover: inherited-valid, direct-valid, neither-invalid.\n\n## Verification\npytest citation-validation tests for the three cases above.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_citation.py","reason":"honor inherited (ancestor) links in citation edge-verify"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py","reason":"inject a parent resolver alongside resolve_deps"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_det_citation_inherited.py","reason":"RED: inherited citation valid via parent depends_on"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","56c0-1d2f-f39c-4ac1"]],"parent_id":"","parent_status_uuid":"aeb0d878-8132-4215-b17c-e4d9fd2836c9","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"a1a2-f491-84e3-4f21","ticket_type":"bug","title":"[rebar:<id>] citation validation should honor inherited hierarchy links","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["cfb71892-5342-48db-b601-501614a5e964","08ee665f-03fe-40fd-892c-ab8affdf3fd1","aeb0d878-8132-4215-b17c-e4d9fd2836c9","b80b3c63-22f1-45c0-9fda-ddc204fdb35c","3f82a0b1-5363-46cb-83da-b343d11d1be3","5cba5550-e1f2-4e8e-98ca-9ca71b21a18a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784778463383234214,"uuid":"d9daa45c-0975-4f89-aa10-16aa8127ee8b"}